  • Overview

    You won’t find a more charming four bedroom Anaheim home on the market for this price! Adjacent to the Colony, this single level home is on a quaint street. The home has been in the same family since the 1950’s as original owners. Before you even enter the home you will see a charming little stained glass window bringing light into the foyer. The home has a great floor plan with arched doorways between the spacious living/dining/family rooms and the bedroom wing. There is a light filled kitchen and separate laundry room (washer and dryer included). It has double paned windows and a slider to the back patio for outdoor dining with family and friends. Lots of room in this gated, low maintenance backyard to play, garden, and add a swimming pool or possibly an ADU. This home has a two car garage with a long driveway, and a work room behind the garage with a separate entrance that you can use as your office or an art studio. Bring your contractor with you to see this home as the kitchen and bathrooms will require work. The air conditioner works great and the original wood floors that are exposed are in good condition; the carpets may be hiding more beautiful wood floors. This home with character is just waiting for your touch to bring it back to its original glory and to make it yours! No HOA, no Mello Roos. Close to Disneyland, Anaheim Packing District, downtown Farmers Market, Founder’s Park and other parks, and the 5, 91, and 57 freeways for an easy commute to anywhere.
